Step-1: Preparation before Facebook Page Create
- Facebook Page Name
- Page Category
- Page Description

Step-2: What we will set in Facebook Page
- Facebook Page Name
- Page Category
- Logo/Profile Picture
- Cover/Banner Picture
- Call To Action (button)
- About section

Step-3: How to search name 
- Idea Generate
- Think and Find a Suitable Name

Step-4: name search in www.leandomainsearch.com

Step-5: Check domain is available or not in www.namecheap.com

Step-6: Search in Facebook, same named page has or not
- login in Your Facebook 
- in top search bar, type your searched name

Step-7: Business Page Create in Facebook
- Login Facebook --> See More --> Pages 

Step-8: click on “Create New Page”
- Page Name: Your Page Name (example:  Solution Level)
- Category: Your Page Category (example: Social Media Marketing)
- Bio: write a short description about your page

Step-9 
- Upload logo/Profile Picture
- Upload Cover/Banner image
- Call To Action (CTA) button
- About

Step-10: New created facebook page will show, do below task

Step-11: add logo/profile pic, banner/cover pic 

Step-12: Add Call To Action button
- all/post click
- click on (...) 3 dot right side --> Call To Action 
- "Contact" click 
- set phone number (+880 01731110386)

Step-13: after set “call now” --> Next 

Step-14: add “About”
Add
- Contact info
- Phone number
- Website: website link
- Social Link:

Step-15: Post -->Add Bio
A Facebook page bio is a short, 101-character description under
your name that summarizes your identity or business

Step-16: Post --> Features (add logo and others photos)

Step-17: About --> Details About 

Step-18: set Username
Click on "settings"
a. Search by “name” 
b. Click on “View or >”
c. Click on “Edit” of Username 
d. Write username (no space between word)
e. Set profile password 

Step-19: Give Page Access (Admin,moderator,…)
a. Click on setting
b. Search by name 
c. Click on “Page Access”
d. Click on “People with task access” --> AddNew
e. Select a person profile, select his/her task
